A thread is a path of execution in a program that goes through the following states of a thread.
The five states are as follows:
1:New
2:Runnable
3:Running
4:Blocked
5:Dead

NewState:
When an instance thread class  created a new thread is created but it is not alive yet.

Runnable state:
Runnable state is a state in which a thread is ready to go to the running state.it may come from new state or blocked or waiting
state.

Running state:
Running state in thread is currently executing. it may go to the blocked state or waiting state or dead state.

Blocked state:
In this state the thread is blocked for specific amount time or waiting for some resource to execute forthere.

Dead state:
After completion of the task the thread go to the dead state in which the thread is dead.
